The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Speeding accident kills 23 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Speeding accident kills 23 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Dhubri, Oct. 14: Twenty-three passengers on a speeding, packed bus died last night when it rammed into a standing truck while trying to avoid another coming from the opposite side.        
	The accident happened around 12.35am on National Highway 31 in Dhubri district. The bus with 67 brick kiln workers  the vehicles capacity is 32 people  overturned by the impact of the crash.         
	A 709 (model) bus has a capacity of 32 passengers but there were 67 of them in the bus, a police official said. A survivor said the bus was speeding.         
	Over 40 people were injured, of which the condition of seven was critical. They were admitted to Gauhati Medical College Hospital.         
	Among the victims, five were women and six children.         
	Police said the bus was on its way to Hojai in Nagaon district from Dhubri district. The site of the accident is 240km from Guwahati.                                                                                                                                                                         
